'cont'=>'January 13, 1953 (Imjin years winter January 28), the Drafting Committee of the Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China was established in Beijing. <br> 1953 1 13 Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China, the Drafting Committee was set up in Beijing, responsible for the drafting of the first constitution in the People&#39;s Republic of China. <br> 1953, the Central People&#39;s Government Committee 20 meeting by a resolution on the convening of the National People&#39;s Congress and local levels of people&#39;s&#39;s Congress. The resolution states that generated by universal suffrage by the people, townships, counties, provinces (municipalities) all levels of people&#39;s Congress was held in 1953, and then held on the basis of the National People&#39;s Congress. This time on the National People&#39;s Congress, the constitution. In order to carry out the work of the drafting of the constitution, the establishment of the Constitution Drafting Committee of the People&#39;s Republic of China, Chairman Mao Zedong. March 24, 1954, the Drafting Committee of the Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China held its first meeting, Chairman Mao Zedong, the CPC Central Committee and the drafting of the draft Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China (draft) \"on behalf of the Chinese Communist Party. Constitution Drafting Committee to accept the preliminary draft of the draft constitution, in Beijing and in some large cities of the country organizations of various democratic parties, people&#39;s organizations and social aspects of a representative figure of more than 8,000 people, more than two months time to discuss on the draft draft based and modified after June 1, 1954, the Constitution Drafting Committee meeting by the draft Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China, will submit the draft to the Central People&#39;s Government Committee for discussion. June 14, the Central People&#39;s Government Committee adopted the draft Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China, decided to publication of the draft referendum discussion to discuss a total of 150 million people participate, which lasted more than two months. On September 9, the Central People&#39;s Government Committee meeting, according to the comments made in the national discussion, discussed and adopted the amended Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China (Draft) \", September 12 the Constitution Drafting Committee discussed and adopted the Constitution Drafting Committee to the first meeting of the first session of the National People&#39;s Congress on the Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China (Draft) \"by the report. Constitution Drafting Committee to the General Assembly on September 15 the first session of the National People&#39;s Congress held its first meeting, the Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China (Draft), on behalf of Liu Shaoqi Constitution Drafting Committee, made a report on the draft Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China . \" The first meeting of the September 20, the first session of the National People&#39;s Congress, elected by secret ballot by the Constitution of the People&#39;s Republic of China \"(that is, the 1954 Constitution). (1 $ dj¦Ó.c¨­m) <br>'
